            <ArticleTitle>Photonic crystal fibers supporting fully separated eigenmodes.</ArticleTitle>
            <Pagination>
                <MedlinePgn>3046-3049</MedlinePgn>
            </Pagination>
            <ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1364/OL.44.003046</ELocationID>
            <Abstract>
                <AbstractText>We present two kinds of fully degeneracy-lifted solid-core photonic crystal multi-mode fibers aiming at multiple-input multiple-output-free direct fiber vector eigenmode multiplexing transmission. One of the target fiber structures is able to support 52 fully separated eigenmodes with effective index difference above 1.37×10<sup>-4</sup> and confinement loss below 3.28×10<sup>-5</sup>  dB/km over the whole C+Lband (1530-1625 nm). Specifically, it is suggested that &gt;10<sup>-4</sup> effective index separation is sufficient to possess polarization-maintaining properties, while for short-reach stable mode-division multiplexing transmission, the effective index difference &gt;10<sup>-3</sup> is highly desired. In particular, the other target fiber structure can further increase effective index separation above 1.10×10<sup>-3</sup> among 24 eigenmodes with confinement loss below 6.68×10<sup>-4</sup>  dB/km over the whole C+L band.</AbstractText>
            </Abstract>
